            <DIV dir=3D"ltr">
            <DIV>The workshop will run a full day, and be divided in two =
parts,=20
            in order to emphasize both theoretical/algorithmic aspects =
and=20
            practical applications. Ample space will be given to peer=20
            discussions and brainstorming about the results of the =
presentations=20
            and the ideas brought forth by participants.</DIV>
            <DIV><BR></DIV>
            <DIV><FONT face=3D"arial, sans-serif" size=3D"2"><B>We are =
honoured to=20
            announce that the keynote will be given by <FONT=20
            color=3D"#3d85c6">Jean-Yves Vion-Dury</FONT>. The title of =
the keynote=20
            is: </B>"</FONT><SPAN style=3D"line-height: 1.6;">Some =
Perspectives on=20
            Change&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN style=3D"line-height: =
1.6;">Management: From=20
            Basic Primitive Tools to Context-Aware Applicative=20
            Components</SPAN><FONT face=3D"arial, sans-serif" =
size=3D"2"><SPAN=20
            style=3D"line-height: 1.6;">"</SPAN></FONT></DIV>
            <DIV><B><BR></B></DIV>
            <DIV><B>List of accepted regular papers:</B></DIV>
            <DIV>
            <UL>
              <LI>Stephen Coakley, Jacob Mischka and Cheng Thao: =
Version-Aware=20
              Word Documents</LI>
              <LI>Dennis Hamilton: Tracked Changes: Navigating the=20
              Document-Format Anti-Pattern</LI>
              <LI>Meenu Pandey, Ethan Munson and Cheng Thao: Progress =
Report on=20
              Version-Aware LibreOffice</LI>
              <LI>Nigel Whitaker: Understanding Changes in N-Way-Merge:=20
              Use-Cases and User Interface Demonstrations</LI></UL>
            <DIV><B>List of accepted work-in-progress &amp; position=20
            papers:</B></DIV></DIV>
            <DIV>
            <UL>
              <LI>Dennis Hamilton: Progress Report: Protected Change=20
              Tracking</LI>
              <LI>Svante Schubert and Patrick Durusau: Untethered, =
Asynchronous=20
              Change Tracking for File Formats</LI>
              <LI>Johannes Wilm and Daniel Frebel: Real-World Challenges =
to=20
              Collaborative Text Creation</LI></UL>
            <DIV><B><FONT size=3D"2"><BR></FONT></B></DIV>
            <DIV><B><FONT size=3D"2">Preliminary=20
            Program:</FONT></B></DIV></DIV><SPAN style=3D"line-height: =
1.6;">
            <UL>
              <LI><SPAN style=3D"line-height: 1.6;"><B>09:00 - 09:30 =
Opening=20
              Session&nbsp;</B></SPAN></LI>
              <LI><SPAN style=3D"line-height: 1.6;"><B>09:30 - 10:30=20
              Keynote&nbsp;</B></SPAN></LI>
              <UL>
                <LI><SPAN style=3D"line-height: 1.6;"><FONT=20
                color=3D"#3d85c6">Jean-Yves Vion-Dury </FONT>Some =
Perspectives on=20
                Change&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN style=3D"line-height: =
1.6;">Management:=20
                From Basic Primitive Tools to Context-Aware Applicative=20
                Components&nbsp;</SPAN></LI></UL>
              <LI><SPAN style=3D"line-height: 1.6;"><B>10:30 - 11:00 =
Coffee=20
              Break&nbsp;</B></SPAN></LI>
              <LI><SPAN style=3D"line-height: 1.6;"><B>11:00 - 12:30 =
Session I:=20
              Research Topics&nbsp;</B></SPAN></LI>
              <UL>
                <LI><SPAN style=3D"line-height: 1.6;"><FONT=20
                color=3D"#3d85c6">Stephen Coakley, Jacob Mischka and =
Cheng=20
                Thao</FONT>&nbsp;Version-Aware Word Documents=20
                (15+5)&nbsp;</SPAN></LI>
                <LI><SPAN style=3D"line-height: 1.6;"><FONT =
